# Coding Standards

## Minimal Changes
- keep changes compact, modify only what's necessary
- avoid refactoring unrelated code

## Code Reuse
- check `src/utils/` before creating new utilities
- reuse: `signal()`, `guard()`, `tryCatch()`, `hash()`, `Linker<T>`
- check `src/config.ts` for constants before hardcoding

## Variable Naming
- short, direct names: `doc`, `uri`, `path`, `file`, `op`
- private members: `_` prefix (e.g., `_files`, `_log`)
- constants: `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE`

## Speed Over Complexity
- prioritize performance, use early returns
- use `Map`/`Set` for O(1) lookups
- add brief comments explaining non-obvious logic

## Comments
- all comments lowercase
- use markers: `// note:`, `// fixme:`, `// todo:`
- keep brief, same line when possible

```typescript
// good
const doc = this._sharedb.get(id);
const [err, data] = await tryCatch(fetchData());
// note: filter duplicates from path array

// bad
const shareDbDocument = this._shareDbConnection.getDocument(assetId);
// This is a comment that should be lowercase
```
